'Connell%20make%20history%20at%20the%20Oscars%20tonight%20as%20they%20became%20the%20youngest%20talents%20to%20win%20two%20Oscars%20under%2030.%20At%20just%2022%20and%2026%2C%20respectively%2C%20the%20sibling%20duo%20won%20their%20second%20Oscar%20for%20the%20'Barbie'%20movie%20song%20'What%20Was%20I%20Made%20For'.%20They%20previously%20won%20for%20the%20James%20Bond%20soundtrack%20'No%20Time%20To%20Die'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Urban%20Employment%20Programmes%3A%20A%20Catalyst%20for%20Female%20Labour%20Force%20Participation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10173957%2Fbelle-maluf-MxF6x11ICWs-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20recent%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20urban%20employment%20landscape%20has%20witnessed%20a%20new%20entrant%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Urban%20Employment%20Programmes%20(UEPs)%2C%20currently%20implemented%20across%20nine%20Indian%20states.%20The%20latest%20offering%20%E2%80%93%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20Indira%20Gandhi%20Rozgar%20Yojna%20(IRGY)%20%E2%80%93%20was%20launched%20in%202022%20with%20an%20ambitious%20Rs%20800-crore%20budget%2C%20to%20address%20issues%20of%20urban%20poverty%2C%20inflation%20and%20joblessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scale%20of%20these%20problems%20is%20large%2C%20and%20gendered.%20India%E2%80%99s%20unemployment%20rate%20remains%20around%208-9%25%2C%20yet%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%20reveals%20that%20only%2021.9%25%20of%20women%20aged%2015%20and%20above%20in%20urban%20areas%20participate%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20with%20a%20significant%2091%25%20employed%20in%20the%20informal%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20UEPs%20across%20India%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1003041%2Fhow-urban-employment-schemes-can-offer-social-security-to-the-poor-and-empower-women%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20note%20the%20predominance%20of%20women%20workers%2C%20and%20our%20research%20in%20Rajasthan%20suggests%20that%20over%2090%25%20of%20IRGY%20beneficiaries%20are%20women.%20These%20metrics%20indicate%20a%20positive%20movement%20towards%20gender%20inclusivity%20and%20empowerment.%20A%20review%20of%20UEPs%20across%20India%20and%20insights%20from%20the%20field%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Odisha%20help%20us%20understand%20what%20draws%20women%20to%20these%20programmes%20and%20identify%20best%20practices%20and%20learnings%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20sustained%20increase%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20contexts%20and%20household%20dynamics%20are%20key%20determinants%20for%20lower%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%20UEPs%20provides%20many%20women%20a%20pathway%20to%20enter%20the%20labour%20market%2C%20hitherto%20unavailable%20due%20to%20limited%20employment%20opportunities%2C%20unpaid%20care%20responsibilities%2C%20and%20other%20limitations%20placed%20by%20households%2C%20such%20as%20distance%20to%20work%2C%20work%20timings%2C%20and%20the%20concerns%20about%20safety%20outside%20the%20home%20and%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUEPs%20address%20these%20issues%20by%20offering%20a%20structured%20and%20supportive%20environment%20for%20women%20to%20enter%20the%20formal%20labour%20market.%20For%20informal%20workers%20such%20as%20home-based%20workers%2C%20UEPs%20substitute%20exploitative%20labour%20and%20wages%20(often%20as%20low%20as%20Rs.%2050%20a%20day)%20with%20a%20guaranteed%20minimum%20wage.%20Domestic%20workers%20benefit%20from%20a%20single%20worksite%2C%20reducing%20time%20and%20cost%20spent%20on%20commuting%2C%20and%20facilitating%20better%20management%20of%20household%20tasks.%20Similarly%2C%20casual%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20those%20in%20construction%2C%20find%20UEPs%20safer%20and%20easier%20to%20access%2C%20even%20if%20wages%20may%20be%20slightly%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22In%20Charts%3A%20How%20Women%20Continue%20to%20Shoulder%20the%20Burden%20of%20Unpaid%20Work%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fin-charts-how-women-continue-to-shoulder-the-burden-of-unpaid-work%5C%22%3EIn%20Charts%3A%20How%20Women%20Continue%20to%20Shoulder%20the%20Burden%20of%20Unpaid%20Work%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUEPs%20also%20offer%20a%20sense%20of%20safety%20for%20women%2C%20as%20many%20reported%20feeling%20safer%20due%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20other%20woman%20at%20the%20worksite.%20Women%20also%20found%20camaraderie%20and%20built%20stronger%20social%20networks%20at%20worksites.%20Ironically%2C%20these%20workspaces%20became%20unexpected%20spaces%20of%20leisure%20granting%20women%20a%20break%20from%20relentless%20household%20responsibilities.%20This%20support%20extended%20beyond%20the%20workday%2C%20with%20women%20forging%20friendships%20that%20helped%20navigate%20personal%20lives%20and%20crises.%20The%20programme%20also%20granted%20women%20a%20degree%20of%20autonomy%20by%20empowering%20them%20with%20financial%20resources%20and%20a%20role%20in%20household%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20social%20contexts%20that%20make%20UEPs%20attractive.%20Informal%20work%20is%20layered%20with%20precarities%2C%20one%20of%20which%20is%20the%20task%20of%20finding%20work%20frequently.%20UEPs%20guarantee%20work%20(up%20to%20125%20days%20in%20Rajasthan)%20and%20often%20back%20this%20promise%20with%20unemployment%20allowances.%20UEPs%20also%20offer%20multiple%20avenues%20for%20workers%20to%20register%20for%20work%2C%20including%20camps%20organised%20by%20Urban%20Local%20Bodies%20and%20Civil%20Society%20Organisations%2C%20online%20registration%2C%20and%20support%20centres%20like%20e-mitra.%20The%20diversity%20of%20options%20and%20quick%20enrolment%20significantly%20reduce%20the%20barriers%20to%20entry%20that%20women%20face%20when%20applying%20for%20other%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20these%20benefits%2C%20UEPs%2C%20face%20criticism%20for%20offering%20lower-than-market%20wages%2C%20and%20for%20excessive%20focus%20on%20manual%20labour%20and%20for%20the%20quality%20of%20employment.%20Considering%20these%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%2C%20we%20recommend%20several%20improvements%20for%20UEPs%20to%20elevate%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroaden%20Eligibility%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Access%20to%20UEPs%20in%20India%20are%20mostly%20restricted%20to%20residents.%20Not%20only%20does%20this%20leave%20out%20migrant%20women%2C%20who%20are%20often%20more%20vulnerable%2C%20but%20also%20long-term%20residents%20who%20may%20be%20considered%20migrants%20%E2%80%98on%20paper%E2%80%99%20and%20unable%20to%20meet%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%2C%20enforced%20through%20requirements%20such%20as%20Aadhaar%2C%20ration%20cards%2C%20or%20voter%20ID%20cards.%20UEPs%20must%20consider%20non-local%20identification%2C%20such%20as%20Aadhaar%2C%20and%20ID%20cards%20generated%20through%20worker%20organisations%20or%20unions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOffer%20Flexible%20Work%20Options%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Recognising%20the%20burden%20of%20household%20work%2C%20UEPs%20can%20offer%20flexible%20work%20options%2C%20allowing%20women%20to%20choose%20shorter%20daily%20shifts%20of%20three%20to%20four%20hours%2C%20or%20condensed%20workweeks%20of%20two%20to%20three%20days.%20Similar%20employment%20programmes%20in%20South%20Africa%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1057%2F9781137313997_4%5C%22%3EArgentina%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20offered%20such%20options.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.levyinstitute.org%2Fpubs%2Fwp_519.pdf%5C%22%3EArgentina%E2%80%99s%20Plan%20Jefes%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20effective%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20beneficiaries%20being%20women.%20Studies%20show%20improved%20access%20to%20social%20services%2C%20reduced%20school%20dropout%20rates%2C%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20abuse%20and%20crime.%20Women%20also%20report%20gaining%20additional%20skills%2C%20improving%20their%20chances%20of%20obtaining%20other%20paid%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Despite%20Talk%20of%20Diversity%2C%20Women%20Still%20a%20Minority%20in%20Indian%20Boardrooms%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fdespite-talk-of-diversity-women-still-a-minority-in-indian-boardrooms%5C%22%3EDespite%20Talk%20of%20Diversity%2C%20Women%20Still%20a%20Minority%20in%20Indian%20Boardrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EExpand%20the%20Scope%20of%20Work%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20UEPs%20must%20target%20an%20expanded%20list%20of%20work%2C%20such%20as%20building%20and%20managing%20economic%20and%20social%20infrastructure%2C%20which%20can%20include%20childcare%20facilities%20(creches)%2C%20canteens%2C%20and%20multi-purpose%20centres%20(MPCCs)%20where%20women%20can%20collectivise%2C%20work%2C%20and%20rest.%20Women%20can%20also%20be%20granted%20work%20in%20community%20kitchens%2C%20and%20educational%20institutions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20public%20institutions%20such%20as%20Anganwaadis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImprove%20Accessibility%20and%20Mobility%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20UEPs%20should%20provide%20work%20closer%20to%20home%20and%20within%20a%201-2%20km%20radius%20to%20minimise%20transit%20time%20and%20cost.%20Alternatively%2C%20a%20transportation%20allowance%20(as%20practiced%20in%20Kerala)%20or%20free-to-use%20public%20transport%20can%20benefit%20women%20workers%20and%20enhance%20their%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrioritise%20Safety%20and%20Comfort%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Many%20women%20prefer%20UEPs%20because%20they%20provide%20safe%20spaces%20for%20decent%20work.%20Workplace%20amenities%20must%20include%20toilets%2C%20resting%20spaces%2C%20drinking%20water%2C%20and%20childcare%20facilities.%20This%20can%20set%20a%20positive%20benchmark%20for%20private%20markets%20as%20well%20and%20increase%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWages%20and%20Skilling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Typically%2C%20UEPs%20are%20aligned%20to%20minimum%20state%20wages.%20However%2C%20states%20must%20consider%20introducing%20the%20concept%20of%20living%20wages%2C%20which%20broadens%20the%20discussion%20on%20wages%20to%20include%20skill%20levels%2C%20and%20account%20for%20input%20factors%20such%20as%20the%20nature%20and%20location%20of%20work.%20A%20model%20such%20as%20this%20will%20additionally%20build%20a%20component%20of%20apprenticeship%2C%20allowing%20new%20and%20unskilled%20workers%20to%20learn%20from%20experienced%20workers%20and%20eventually%20find%20e%20permanent%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20UEPs%20are%20a%20vital%20lifeline%20for%20many%20women%20in%20urban%20India%2C%20high%20uptake%20should%20not%20be%20the%20end%20goal.%20UEPs%20must%20go%20beyond%20being%20safety%20nets%2C%20to%20imbibe%20not%20just%20protective%20and%20preventive%20measures%2C%20but%20transformative%20measures%20that%20address%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation.%20This%20will%20need%20UEPs%20to%20adopt%20a%20more%20innovative%20approach%2C%20offering%20better%20wages%2C%20an%20expansive%20set%20of%20contextualised%20works%2C%20greater%20access%2C%20as%20well%20as%20safety%20and%20dignity.%20The%20true%20measure%20of%20success%20lies%20in%20building%20upon%20this%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVrashali%20Khandelwal%20is%20a%20Consultant%20at%20Indian%20Institute%20for%20Human%20Settlements%20(IIHS)%20and%20her%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ework%20revolves%20around%20issues%20of%20informality%20and%20social%20protection.%20Sukrit%20Nagpal%20is%20a%20researcher%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Epractitioner%20at%20IIHS%20and%20his%20work%20focuses%20on%20urban%20housing%20and%20informal%20work.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710122452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10173957%2Fbelle-maluf-MxF6x11ICWs-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Furban-employment-programmes-a-catalyst-for-female-labour-force-participation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Urban%20employment%20programmes%20must%20go%20beyond%20being%20safety%20nets%2C%20to%20imbibe%20not%20just%20protective%20and%20preventive%20measures%2C%20but%20transformative%20measures%20that%20address%20women%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20participation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Furban-employment-programmes-a-catalyst-for-female-labour-force-participation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blog%3A%20In%20Manipur%2C%20To%20SoO%20Or%20Not%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20tripartite%20agreement%20signed%20in%202008%20between%20two%20dozen%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20and%20the%20Manipur%20government%20and%20the%20Centre%20ended%20on%20February%2029%2C%202024.%20On%20the%20same%20day%2C%20the%20Manipur%20government%20passed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fend-suspension-of-operations-soo-agreement-with-all-kuki-zo-insurgent-groups-manipur-assembly-in-unanimous-resolution-5150821%5C%22%3Eunanimous%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20assembly%20to%20scrap%20-%20i.e.%20not%20to%20renew%20-%20what%20is%20known%20as%20the%20Suspension%20of%20Operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20in%20the%20border%20state%20marred%20by%20ethnic%20violence%20between%20the%20hill-majority%20Kuki-Zo%20tribes%20and%20the%20valley-majority%20Meiteis.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20the%20Centre%20said%20it%20is%20yet%20to%20decide%20on%20continuing%20the%20controversial%20ceasefire%20deal%2C%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20this%20agreement%2C%20the%20insurgents%20are%20to%20stay%20at%20designated%20camps%20and%20their%20weapons%20kept%20in%20locked%20storage%2C%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faerial-pics-of-manipur-insurgent-camps-as-army-conducts-surprise-checks-4088722%5C%22%3Emonitored%20regularly%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Insurgents%20who%20are%20part%20of%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20get%20a%20stipend%20of%20Rs%206%2C000%20every%20month%2C%20meant%20for%20their%20rehabilitation.%20The%20agreement%20is%20also%20reviewed%20every%20year%20for%20extension%20or%20termination%20by%20a%20joint%20monitoring%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20over%20two%20dozen%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20come%20under%20two%20umbrella%20organisations%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20negotiations%20-%20the%20Kuki%20National%20Organisation%20(KNO)%20led%20by%20the%20Kuki%20National%20Army%2C%20and%20the%20United%20People's%20Front%20(UPF)%20led%20by%20the%20Zomi%20Revolutionary%20Army.%20The%20KNO%20and%20the%20UPF%20representing%20all%20the%20others%20have%20signed%20the%20SoO%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20the%20SoO%20Agreement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20peace%20brings%20development%2C%20or%20development%20brings%20peace%2C%20it%20does%20not%20matter%20in%20Manipur%3B%20either%20is%20fine%20for%20a%20start.%20With%20this%20as%20the%20foundation%2C%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20was%20supposed%20to%20bring%20peace%20in%20Manipur%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20hill%20areas.%20The%20government's%20spending%20on%20counterinsurgency%20would%20gradually%20decrease%2C%20which%20would%20in%20turn%20reduce%20the%20feeling%20of%20neglect%20among%20the%20local%20population.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20causes%20of%20insurgency%20is%20lack%20of%20economic%20development%2C%20which%20erodes%20trust%20in%20both%20the%20state%20and%20the%20central%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20camp%20of%20an%20insurgent%20group%20that%20has%20signed%20the%20suspension%20of%20operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20in%20Manipurs%20Chongkhawzao%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20camp%20of%20an%20insurgent%20group%20that%20has%20signed%20the%20suspension%20of%20operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20in%20Manipurs%20Chongkhawzao%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Ftjrt16go_manipur-insurgent-camp-soo_625x300_02_June_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20camp%20of%20an%20insurgent%20group%20that%20has%20signed%20the%20'suspension%20of%20operations'%20(SoO)%20agreement%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20early%2090s%2C%20successive%20governments%20have%20signed%20agreements%20with%20insurgent%20groups%20in%20the%20northeast%20region%20to%20end%20violence%20and%20bring%20stability.%20Though%20insurgents%20have%20been%20the%20signatories%2C%20the%20centre%20of%20gravity%20of%20these%20agreements%20have%20been%20the%20common%20public%2C%20the%20real%20beneficiaries%20of%20peace.%20Happy%20people%20do%20not%20take%20up%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbodo-agreement-signed-amit-shah-says-historic-accord-2170313%5C%22%3Ehuge%20success%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Bodo%20peace%20talks%2C%20and%20understanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplainer-what-is-the-ulfa-peace-deal-and-why-it-is-important-4762189%5C%22%3Esigned%20with%20a%20section%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20insurgent%20group%20United%20Liberation%20Front%20of%20Asom%20(ULFA)%20has%20led%20to%20Assam's%20rapid%20development%3B%20some%20say%20this%20northeast%20state%20saw%20growth%20in%20all%20key%20indicators%20in%20just%2015%20years%20what%20it%20would%20have%20otherwise%20taken%2030%20years.%C2%A0Another%20Assam%20peace%20deal%20signed%20with%20the%20Dimasa%20National%20Liberation%20Army%20in%20April%202023%20brought%20the%20curtain%20down%20on%20the%20Dimasa%20insurgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20neighbouring%20Manipur%20too%2C%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20state%20signed%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20with%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%2C%20made%20ground%20rules%2C%20and%20budgeted%20for%20rehabilitation%20stipend%20without%20fixing%20a%20deadline%20to%20end%20the%20agreement%20for%20good%20should%20the%20process%20fail.%20But%20the%20results%20today%20in%20no%20unclear%20terms%20prove%20that%20the%20Manipur%20SoO%20agreement%20achieved%20quite%20the%20opposite%20of%20what%20Assam%20achieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConcerns%20Over%20Alleged%20Ground%20Rules%20Violations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManipur%20Security%20Adviser%20Kuldiep%20Singh%20has%20said%20attendance%20at%20the%20designated%20camps%20of%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20signatories%20-%20or%20%26quot%3BSoO%20groups%26quot%3B%20in%20short%20-%20has%20not%20been%20100%20per%20cent.%20The%20SoO%20groups%20and%20a%20dozen%20others%20including%20unknown%20fly-by-night%20civil%20society%20organisations%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fillegal-highway-tax-hawala-and-price-rise-are-manipurs-biggest-silent-problem-4393522%5C%22%3Eallegedly%20collecting%20%26quot%3Bgoonda%20tax%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%26quot%3Bprotection%20money%26quot%3B%20from%20truck%20drivers%20and%20transport%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extortion%20amount%20is%20based%20on%20the%20number%20of%20wheels%20the%20truck%20has%20and%20the%20value%20of%20goods%20it%20is%20carrying.%20The%20minimum%20is%20allegedly%20Rs%2030%2C000%20per%20trip%2C%20not%20a%20small%20sum%20for%20a%20single%20truck%20considering%20fuel%20cost%2C%20driver%20salary%2C%20and%20repair%20and%20maintenance.%20It%20needs%20to%20be%20investigated%20whether%20the%20SoO%20groups%20have%20been%20quietly%20'working'%20in%20areas%20where%20the%20authorities%20have%20set%20up%20their%20designated%20camps%2C%20nearly%2014%20in%20all%2C%20in%20the%20hills%20surrounding%20the%20valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fq6v4eko_manipur-insurgent-camp-soo_625x300_02_June_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20camp%20of%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20that%20have%20signed%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20in%20Manipur%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20the%20SoO%20groups%20appear%20to%20be%20taking%20advantage%20of%20gaps%20inherent%20in%20the%20agreement's%20ground%20rules%20as%20well%20as%20the%20rules%20of%20engagement%20(RoE)%20followed%20by%20the%20security%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20security%20forces%20follow%20a%20separate%20RoE%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20dealing%20with%20the%20SoO%20groups.%20Unless%20they%20are%20attacked%20or%20directly%20threatened%20by%20the%20SoO%20groups%2C%20the%20security%20forces%20will%20look%20the%20other%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Lieutenant%20General%20L%20Nishikanta%20Singh%20(retired)%2C%20the%20third%20person%20from%20the%20northeast%20to%20have%20attained%20the%20second-highest%20rank%20in%20the%20Indian%20Army%2C%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsing%20such%20'immunity'%2C%20the%20SoO%20groups%20continue%20to%20build%20up%20their%20strength%2C%20get%20weapons%20like%20sniper%20rifles%20and%20rocket%20launchers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lt%20General%20Singh%2C%20who%20also%20headed%20the%20army's%20Intelligence%20Corps%20before%20retiring%20in%202018%2C%20after%2040%20years%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Visible%20Results%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20visible%20positive%20ripple%20effect%20such%20as%20reduction%20in%20violence%20owing%20to%20the%20SoO%20agreement.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20activism%20by%20SoO%20groups%20has%20only%20increased.%20Leaders%20linked%20to%20the%20SoO%20groups%20and%20the%20umbrella%20organisations%20are%20known%20to%20have%20family%20members%20who%20are%20active%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManipur%20BJP%20MLA%20Nemcha%20Kipgen's%20husband%20Semtinthang%20Kipgen%20alias%20Semma%20T%20Thangboi%20Kipgen%20-%20also%20mentioned%20as%20Semma%20Kipgen%20in%20her%20affidavit%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20-%20heads%20the%20Kuki%20National%20Front%20(P).%20Kuki%20People's%20Alliance%20MLA%20Kimneo%20Hangshing%20is%20the%20wife%20of%20David%20Hangshing%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20insurgent%20group%20Kuki%20Revolutionary%20Army%20(KRA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crores%20of%20rupees%20spent%20on%20trying%20to%20rehabilitate%20the%20insurgents%20of%20the%20SoO%20groups%20are%20taxpayers'%20money.%20Starting%20April%201%2C%202018%2C%20the%20monthly%20stipend%20of%20Rs%206%2C000%20for%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgents%20who%20have%20signed%20this%20agreement%20were%20to%20be%20paid%20after%20linking%20their%20Aadhaar%20biometric%20details%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General's%20(CAG)%20guidelines%20for%20reimbursement%20of%20security-related%20expenses.%20A%20report%20by%20the%20CAG%20which%20was%20presented%20to%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%20on%20March%201%2C%20however%2C%20flagged%20payments%20made%20to%20the%20insurgents%20between%20April%201%2C%202018%20and%20March%2031%2C%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmanipur-soo-agreement-linked-insurgent-leaders-allegedly-diverted-stipend-for-cadres-rehabilitation-says-sources-5169177%5C%22%3Ewithout%20taking%20their%20biometric%20details%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Aadhaar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20payments%20were%20made%20to%20the%20representatives%20of%20the%20cadres%20by%20cheque.%20There%20was%20no%20record%20for%20unique%20biometric%20identification%20number%20linking%20of%20the%20cadres.%20Thus%2C%20payment%20of%20Rs%2027.38%20crore%20to%20the%20cadres%20was%20irregular%20payment%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20guidelines%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CAG%20report%20presented%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20said.%20The%20CAG%20report%20termed%20as%20%26quot%3Bnot%20acceptable%26quot%3B%20the%20reply%20by%20the%20authorities%20who%20handle%20the%20payments%20that%20the%20insurgents%20have%20not%20given%20their%20biometric%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fq90j60ng_manipur-generic_625x300_05_March_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%2025-odd%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20has%20their%20own%20leader%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20two%20representative%20umbrella%20organisations%20that%20are%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20state%20government.%20These%20leaders%20need%20to%20be%20in%20control%20of%20the%20cadre%20to%20ensure%20they%20follow%20the%20ground%20rules%20of%20the%20agreement%2C%20a%20source%20who%20has%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter%20told%20NDTV%20on%20March%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20stipend%20goes%20to%20the%20bank%20accounts%20of%20the%20insurgent%20cadre%20directly%2C%20then%20the%20role%20of%20their%20leaders%20may%20diminish%20as%20they%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20dependent%20on%20the%20few%20leaders%20to%20distribute%20the%20stipend%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20source%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20how%20can%20we%20possibly%20know%20how%20exactly%20the%20leaders%20distribute%20the%20stipend%3F%20The%20insurgent%20leaders%20who%20control%20the%20stipend%20disbursal%20can%20control%20the%20cadre.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20signing%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20and%20dropping%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20money%20into%20the%20pit%20of%20hope%2C%20the%20hold%20of%20insurgents%20on%20the%20public%20appears%20to%20have%20increased.%20These%20groups%20have%20also%20publicly%20instigated%20communities%20in%20Manipur%20to%20hate%20each%20other%2C%20when%20the%20net%20result%20of%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20should%20have%20been%20development%20and%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20cut%20a%20long%20horror%20story%20short%2C%20since%202008%2C%20when%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20was%20formally%20signed%2C%20crores%20of%20rupees%20have%20been%20spent%20on%20stipends%3B%20the%20public%20continues%20to%20be%20harassed%20though%20extortion%20and%20intimidation%2C%20and%20the%20RoE%20doesn't%20easily%20allow%20the%20security%20forces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fvideo-manipur-standoff-between-armoured-vehicle-and-suspected-insurgents-5033646%5C%22%3Eto%20detect%20ground%20rules%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20SoO%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Former%20Chief%20Minister%20Said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20most%20devastating%20is%20the%20admission%20by%20former%20Manipur%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20Congress%20leader%20Okram%20Ibobi%20Singh%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20on%20March%201%20that%20the%20Assam%20Rifles%20and%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20signed%20an%20agreement%20in%202005%20-%20without%20informing%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20two%20signed%20the%20agreement%20without%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20Manipur%20government.%20The%20police%20continued%20to%20arrest%20the%20insurgents%2C%20and%20in%202008%20the%20formal%20SoO%20with%20the%20state%20government's%20participation%20was%20signed%2C%26quot%3B%20Ibobi%20Singh%20told%20the%20assembly.%20The%20state%20government%20discovered%20the%20existence%20of%20the%202005%20%26quot%3Bceasefire%26quot%3B%20agreement%20when%2C%20during%20police%20operations%20against%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgents%2C%20the%20state%20forces%20were%20often%20requested%20to%20stand%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F4l5tjo58_manipur-generic_625x300_28_February_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20differentiates%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgent%20groups%20from%20Naga%20and%20Meitei%20groups%20is%20that%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgents%20only%20want%20a%20%26quot%3Bseparate%20administration%26quot%3B%20carved%20out%20of%20Manipur%2C%20and%20not%20sovereignty%20from%20India%2C%20while%20the%20National%20Socialist%20Council%20of%20Nagaland%20(NSCN)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-extends-ban-on-9-meitei-extremist-groups-in-manipur-for-5-years-4570526%5C%22%3Ebanned%20Meitei%20groups%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20the%20People's%20Revolutionary%20Army%20(PLA)%20want%20to%20break%20away%20from%20India.%20The%20Kuki-Zo%20insurgents%20have%20not%20fought%20against%20the%20army%2C%20but%20the%20NSCN%20faction%20and%20many%20Meitei%20insurgent%20groups%20that%20are%20not%20part%20of%20any%20peace%20talks%20have%20attacked%20Indian%20security%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETen%20Kuki-Zo%20MLAs%20have%20also%20demanded%20separation%20from%20Manipur%2C%20so%20have%20their%20civil%20society%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Indigenous%20Tribal%20Leaders%20Forum%20(ITLF)%20and%20the%20Committee%20on%20Tribal%20Unity%20(CoTU).%20This%20single%20demand%20has%20brought%20the%20SoO%20groups%2C%20the%2010%20Kuki-Zo%20MLAs%2C%20and%20the%20civil%20society%20organisations%20on%20the%20same%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SoO%20agreement%2C%20hence%2C%20concerns%20only%20the%20state%20and%20not%20the%20nation%20since%20the%20insurgents%20are%20not%20demanding%20separation%20from%20India%2C%20but%20from%20Manipur.%20This%20gives%20the%20state%20government%20the%20first%20right%20to%20review%20any%20major%20decision%20linked%20to%20the%20SoO%20groups%20since%20the%20agreement%20directly%20affects%20the%20state%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhich%20is%20why%20the%20only%20certainty%20amid%20the%20whole%20mess%20in%20Manipur%20is%20that%20those%20who%20think%20the%20SoO%20agreement%20review%20and%20the%20demand%20f