through%20a%20blood%20test.%3Cp%3EDIGICOMPHOTO%2FSCIENCE%20PHOTO%20LIBRARY%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20study%20measured%20the%20age%20of%20specific%20organs%20in%205%2C676%20adults%20and%20found%20that%2020%25%20had%20advanced%20aging%20in%20one.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20those%20with%20accelerated%20heart%20aging%20have%20a%20250%25%20higher%20risk%20of%20heart%20failure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%20builds%20on%20the%20idea%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-maximum-age-of-humans-115-or-older-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bbiological%20age%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20measure%20of%20your%20age%20based%20on%20biochemistry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20suggests%20age%20is%20more%20than%20just%20a%20number.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbryan-johnson-45-reduced-biological-age-5-years-project-blueprint-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emultimillionaire%20Bryan%20Johnson%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20paper%2C%20he's%2046%20years%20old.%20But%20he's%20been%20making%20headlines%20by%20contesting%20the%20idea%20that%20it%20means%20something%20about%20his%20health%20%E2%80%94%20and%20lifespan.%20Through%20a%20rigorous%20antiaging%20regimen%20that%20involves%20eating%20a%20strict%20vegan%20diet%2C%20exercising%20regularly%2C%20and%20taking%20more%20than%20100%20pills%20a%20day%2C%20Johnson's%20doctors%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2023-01-25%2Fanti-aging-techniques-taken-to-extreme-by-bryan-johnson%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehis%20test%20results%20show%20that%20he's%20achieved%20the%20heart%20of%20a%2037-year-old%2C%20the%20skin%20of%20a%2028-year-old%2C%20and%20the%20lung%20capacity%20of%20an%2018-year-old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20old%20is%20he%2C%20exactly%3F%20Johnson's%20doctors%20told%20Bloomberg%20that%20he's%20reduced%20his%20%26quot%3Bbiological%20age%26quot%3B%20by%20about%20five%20years.%20Biological%20age%20has%20become%20a%20buzzword%20in%20longevity%20circles%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20true%20age%20that%20our%20cells%2C%20tissues%2C%20and%20organ%20systems%20appear%20to%20be%2C%20based%20on%20biochemistry%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nia.nih.gov%2Fnews%2Fepigenetics-aging-what-bodys-hands-time-tell-us%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dbiological%2520age%2520means%2520the%2520true%2520age%2520that%2520our%2520cells%252C%2520tissues%252C%2520and%2520organ%2520systems%2520appear%2520to%2520be%252C%2520based%2520on%2520biochemistry.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Aging.%20But%20the%20idea%20that%20a%20singular%20number%20can%20represent%20it%20is%20controversial%20partly%20because%20there's%20no%20standard%20for%20normal%20aging%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-the-maximum-age-of-humans-115-or-older-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20Johnson's%20test%20results%20prove%20that%20organs%20don't%20all%20age%20at%20the%20same%20rate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20breakthrough%20in%20longevity%20research%20suggests%20there%20may%20be%20a%20way%20to%20measure%20the%20age%20of%20specific%20organs.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D452b24525b8a55a4c42ac0f5e6c5064280dadf8b4b7f9c1c6b71fa8e1492bf07%26postID%3D65edfdee48eec3d3e783e419%26postSlug%3Dorgan-age-wsj-study-nature-biological-age-longevity-bryan-johnson-2024-3%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06802-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Nature%20utilized%20machine%20learning%20models%20to%20analyze%20the%20age%20of%2011%20major%20organs%20for%205%2C676%20adults.%20One%20of%20the%20study's%20key%20findings%20was%20that%20about%2020%25%20of%20people%20had%20accelerated%20aging%20in%20one%20organ%2C%20associated%20with%20a%2020%20to%2050%25%20higher%20mortality%20risk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20your%20%26quot%3Boldest%20organ%26quot%3B%20might%20also%20tell%20you%20more%20about%20your%20health%20trajectory%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20age-related%20diseases%20you%20could%20develop%20%E2%80%94%20than%20your%20biological%20age.%20The%20study%20found%20that%20individuals%20with%20accelerated%20heart%20aging%2C%20for%20example%2C%20have%20a%20250%25%20higher%20risk%20of%20heart%20failure.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEvery%20additional%20four%20years%20of%20age%20increased%20an%20individual's%20risk%20of%20developing%20heart%20disease%20by%20almost%202.5-fold%20over%2015%20years%2C%20the%20study%20noted.%20It%20also%20found%20that%20accelerated%20brain%20and%20vascular%20aging%20in%20an%20individual%20can%20predict%20the%20progression%20of%20Alzheimer's%20disease%20as%20strongly%20as%20the%20best%20biomarker%20test%20for%20the%20disease.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20technology%20to%20measure%20age%20organ-by-organ%20is%20far%20from%20ready%20to%20mainstream.%20Still%2C%20the%20concept%20has%20attracted%20the%20interest%20of%20those%20in%20longevity%20circles%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fwellness%2Faging-biological-age-organs-health-9b6a4798%3Fmod%3Dhp_lead_pos11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20researchers%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20there%20may%20be%20a%20day%20when%20patients%20can%20test%20the%20age%20of%20their%20organs%20through%20a%20simple%20blood%20test.%C2%A0It's%20not%20a%20far-off%20idea%2C%20given%20that%20there%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancer-detecting-blood-tests-are-set-to-hit-the-market-by-2022-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblood%20tests%20that%20can%20test%20for%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20scientists%20believe%20there's%20little%20merit%20in%20providing%20patients%20with%20these%20details%20before%20we%20devise%20interventions%20for%20them.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20terribly%20helpful%20for%20someone%20to%20know%20they%20might%20arguably%20get%20a%20particular%20age-related%20disease%20early%20unless%20there%20are%20preventive%20steps%20or%20other%20interventions%20they%20can%20take%20to%20help%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20James%20Kirkland%2C%20a%20physician%20and%20professor%20whose%20research%20focuses%20on%20aging%20at%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%2C%20told%20the%20Journal.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forgan-age-wsj-study-nature-biological-age-longevity-bryan-johnson-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710111100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65edff9790413ab8e1db3b48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forgan-age-wsj-study-nature-biological-age-longevity-bryan-johnson-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22New%20research%20finds%20that%20those%20with%20accelerated%20heart%20aging%2C%20for%20example%2C%20have%20a%20250%25%20higher%20risk%20of%20heart%20failure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forgan-age-wsj-study-nature-biological-age-longevity-bryan-johnson-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BJP%20brass%20summons%20top%20Odisha%20netas%20to%20Delhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710109867000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108