n's%20doubles%20badminton%20title%20at%20the%20tournament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20Oldest%20Bread%20Found%20in%20Turkey%2C%20Dating%20Back%208%2C600%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20groundbreaking%20discovery%2C%20archaeologists%20in%20Turkey%20unearthed%20what%20they%20believe%20to%20be%20the%20world's%20oldest%20bread.%20The%20find%20dates%20back%20to%20an%20impressive%206600%20BC%20and%20was%20located%20at%20Catalhoyuk%2C%20an%20archaeological%20site%20in%20southern%20Turkey's%20Konya%20province.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bread%20residue%20was%20found%20near%20a%20partially%20destroyed%20oven%20structure%20in%20an%20area%20called%20%26quot%3BMekan%2066%2C%26quot%3B%20surrounded%20by%20ancient%20mudbrick%20houses.%20According%20to%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.erbakan.edu.tr%2Fhaber%2Fcatalhoyukte-bulunan-8-bin-600-yillik-ekmegin-analizleri-universitemizde-yapildi%2F5869%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20press%20release%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Turkey's%20Necmettin%20Erbakan%20University%20Science%20and%20Technology%20Research%20and%20Application%20Center%20(BITAM)%2C%20the%20bread%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20round%2C%20spongy%20remnant%20and%20was%20identified%20through%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20determined%20that%20the%20organic%20residue%20was%208%2C600-year-old%2C%20uncooked%2C%20fermented%20bread%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F03%2F08%2Fmiddleeast%2Fworlds-oldest-bread-discovered-turkey-intl-scli-scn%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20say%20that%20this%20finds%20at%20Catalhoyuk%20is%20the%20oldest%20bread%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20archaeologist%20Ali%20Umut%20Turkcan%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Excavation%20Delegation%20and%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Anadolu%20University%20in%20Turkey%2C%20told%20Turkish%20state%20news%20outlet%20Anadolu%20Agency%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20smaller%20version%20of%20a%20loaf%20of%20bread.%20It%20has%20a%20finger%20pressed%20in%20the%20center%2C%20it%20has%20not%20been%20baked%2C%20but%20it%20has%20been%20fermented%20and%20has%20survived%20to%20the%20present%20day%20with%20the%20starches%20inside.%20There%20is%20no%20similar%20example%20of%20something%20like%20this%20to%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMicroscopic%20analysis%20confirmed%20the%20team's%20suspicions.%20Images%20from%20a%20scanning%20electron%20microscope%20revealed%20air%20spaces%20and%20identifiable%20starch%20granules%20within%20the%20sample.%20Salih%20Kavak%2C%20a%20biologist%20at%20Gaziantep%20University%20in%20Turkey%2C%20explained%20in%20the%20press%20release%20that%20this%20finding%20%26quot%3Beliminated%20our%20doubts%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20bread's%20authenticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20analysis%20revealed%20the%20chemical%20makeup%20of%20the%20sample%2C%20including%20both%20plant%20material%20and%20indicators%20of%20fermentation.%20This%20suggests%20that%20flour%20and%20water%20were%20combined%20to%20create%20the%20dough%2C%20which%20was%20then%20prepared%20near%20the%20oven%20and%20likely%20stored%20for%20some%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20exciting%20discovery%20for%20Turkey%20and%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Kavak%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20thin%20layer%20of%20clay%20encasing%20the%20structure%20acted%20as%20a%20preservative%20for%20organic%20materials%20like%20wood%20and%20bread%2C%20explains%20archaeologist%20Turkcan.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710092460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F39k9fplg_worlds-oldest-bread_625x300_10_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fworlds-oldest-bread-found-in-turkey-dating-back-8-600-years-5213972%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20b