United%20States%2C%20to%20a%20degree%20that%20simply%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20possible%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20century%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fgovernance%2Frich-land-poor-people-what-will-be-the-future-of-generations-growing-up-in-jharkhand-s-coal-belt-89534%5C%22%3Ecoal%20companies%20have%20taken%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DC33Wfhu3BX0%5C%22%3Escorched%20the%20ground%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Jharia%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20turning%20what%20had%20been%20a%20home%20to%20Adivasi%20communities%20into%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DUzivaxYf1iM%5C%22%3Euninhabitable%20hellscape%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20of%20those%20who%20thereby%20lost%20their%20lands%20and%20livelihoods%20became%20coal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2019%2F10%2Fthe-burning-coalfields-of-jharia-belch-poison-for-local-residents%2F%5C%22%3Eminers%2C%20who%20today%20remain%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F05%2Ffear-of-job-loss-and-social-security-run-high-among-jharkhand-mine-workers%2F%5C%22%3Epool%20of%20unsupported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1043473%2Ftheyve-nothing-else-here-the-poor-steal-coal-in-jharkhands-mining-hubs-in-order-to-survive%5C%22%3Eimpoverished%20labourers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20daily%20exposed%20to%20toxic%20levels%20of%20pollution%E2%80%94even%20as%20they%20remain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiforest.global%2F2020%2F11%2Fjharkhand-contributes-to-32-of-the-countrys-reserves-but-loses-more-than-it-gains-from-coal%2F%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20most%20underserved%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20electrification%20they%20bring%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%94a%20prime%20example%20of%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fbusiness-technology%2Fnone-of-the-worlds-top-industries-would-be-profitable-if-they-paid-for-the-natural-capital-they-use%2F%5C%22%3Ereal%20costs%20are%20absorbed%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20those%20on%20the%20peripheries%2C%20while%20benefits%20accrue%20in%20the%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPetroleum%E2%80%99s%20higher%20energy%20density%20shrank%20the%20space%20needed%20to%20carry%20fuel%20and%20expanded%20cargo%20space.%20It%20made%20possible%20the%20vast%20modern%20fleets%20of%20enormous%20shipping%20vessels%2C%20each%20carrying%20multiple%20trainloads%20of%20goods%20halfway%20around%20the%20world%20in%20a%20just%20a%20few%20weeks.%20Petroleum%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20build%20and%20sell%20billions%20of%20scooters%20and%20cars%20and%20trucks%20that%20could%20ferry%20people%20and%20goods%20to%20any%20remote%20little%20town%20or%20village%20left%20behind%20by%20rail%20networks.%20Petroleum%20paved%20the%20roads%20to%20reach%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20food%20systems%20also%20became%20intimately%20tied%20to%20the%20abundance%20of%20cheap%20oil%2C%20from%20making%20artificial%20pesticides%2C%20and%20herbicides%E2%80%94upon%20which%20industrial%20agriculture%20depends%E2%80%94to%20the%20long-distance%20transport%20chains%20that%20get%20farm%20produce%20to%20consumers.%20The%20modern%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.postcarbon.org%2Fpublications%2Ffood-and-farming-transition%2F%5C%22%3Eindustrial%20food%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20requires%2C%20on%20average%2C%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Ffigure%2FEnergy-expended-in-producing-and-delivering-one-food-calorie-Approximately-73-calories_fig1_303895662%5C%22%3Eseven%20calories%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20energy%20expenditure%20for%20each%20calorie%20that%20it%20delivers%20to%20our%20plates.%20Petroleum%20made%20modern%20mining%20operations%20possible%20too%2C%20multiplying%20the%20rate%20of%20extraction%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visualcapitalist.com%2Fall-the-worlds-metals-and-minerals-in-one-visualization%2F%5C%22%3Eiron%2C%20copper%2C%20sand%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20everything%20else%E2%80%94including%20more%20coal%20and%20petroleum.%20Petroleum%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20fly%20passenger%20(or%20war)%20planes%2C%20connecting%20(or%20killing)%20people%20around%20the%20world%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20oil-based%20economy%20allows%20labor%2C%20capital%2C%20raw%20materials%2C%20and%20goods%20to%20move%20more%20rapidly%20along%20much%20the%20same%20pathways%20that%20were%20established%20during%20the%20centuries%20of%20European%20colonialism%3A%20materials%20and%20labor%20extracted%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20accumulate%20their%20benefits%20in%20the%20Global%20North%20faster%20than%20ever.%20Those%20pathways%20are%20kept%20open%20by%20oil-guzzling%2C%20industrialised%20militaries.%20Oil%2C%20itself%2C%20is%20also%20the%20source%20of%20huge%20quantities%20of%20cheap%20raw%20materials%20that%20further%20bolster%20industrialism%20by%20providing%20wholly%20novel%20materials%2C%20now%20essential%20to%20our%20lives%3A%20plastics%2C%20coatings%2C%20lubricants%2C%20solvents%2C%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20dyes%2C%20textiles%2C%20and%20more.%20And%20it%20does%20this%20at%20a%20cost%20unmatchable%20by%20any%20other%20material%20or%20process%20available%20on%20Earth.%20It%20is%20the%20lifeblood%20of%20the%20industrial%20economy.%20And%20the%20control%20of%20its%20production%2C%20distribution%2C%20and%20acquisition%20is%20a%20principle%20driver%20of%20modern%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10113314%2FNHQ202211160200large.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fu