%2F5301%2F2023%2Fessd-15-5301-2023.html)%3B%20Global%20Carbon%20Project%202023%20(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalcarbonproject.org%2Fcarbonbudget%2F)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20already%20built%20a%20world%20that%E2%80%99s%20now%20well%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Estate%20of%20ecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20locked%20into%20capitalism%E2%80%99s%20requirement%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%5C%22%3Egrowth%20in%20consumption%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20to%20keep%20the%20present%20system%20afloat%3A%20to%20keep%20the%20goods%20flowing%2C%20the%20steel%20and%20concrete%20rising%2C%20the%20institutions%20flush%20with%20resources%20for%20research%20and%20education%20and%20policymaking%2C%20the%20factories%20supplied%20with%20raw%20materials%20and%20industrial%20chemicals%E2%80%94many%20of%20which%20are%20directly%20sourced%20from%20petroleum.%20As%20a%20living%20system%20set%20upon%20a%20trajectory%20of%20unabated%20growth%2C%20our%20economy%20requires%20the%20massive%20overconsumption%20of%20both%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20even%20as%20it%20destroys%20the%20living%20systems%20of%20the%20world%20upon%20which%20it%20depends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20crux%20of%20our%20predicament%3A%20Consumption%2C%20growth%2C%20socioeconomic%20wellbeing%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20inequalities%2C%20exploitation%2C%20pollution%2C%20species%20genocide%2C%20ecosystem%20annihilation%2C%20and%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20form%20a%20nexus%20of%20interdependencies%20that%20feed%20and%20perpetuate%20one%20another%20as%20the%20basis%20of%20modern%20global%20civilisation.%20This%20system%20is%20both%20unsustainable%20over%20time%20as%20well%20as%20immediately%20destructive%20for%20great%20multitudes%2C%20both%20human%20and%20non-human%2C%20even%20while%20we%20have%20made%20it%20foundational%20to%20the%20dreams%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20billions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20deployed%20thirsty%2C%20high-yielding%20strains%20of%20wheat%20and%20rice%20that%20grew%20well%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20artificial%20fertilisers%2C%20herbicides%2C%20and%20pesticides.%20As%20with%20any%20%E2%80%98progress%20trap%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20short-term%20benefits%20gained%20cannot%20overcome%20the%20long-term%20costs%20incurred%2C%20including%20soil%20destruction%3B%20groundwater%20depletion%3B%20chemical%20pollution%20of%20land%2C%20water%2C%20and%20people%3B%20loss%20of%20insects%20and%20other%20biodiversity%3B%20narrowing%20of%20the%20Indian%20diet%3B%20and%20extinction%20of%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fgrains-of-life-how-chotanagpurs-adivasis-are-reviving-native-varieties-of-rice%5C%22%3Eone%20lakh%20varieties%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20indigenous%20seeds%2C%20shrinking%20the%20available%20gene%20pool%20for%20food%20grains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20combustible%20fossil%20revolution%E2%80%94with%20a%20special%20emphasis%20on%20oil%E2%80%94absolutely%20underwrites%20the%20modern%20way%20of%20life.%20It%20has%20provided%20continuous%20growth%20in%20energy%20use%2C%20which%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20replicated%20by%20less%20concentrated%2C%20more%20unreliable%2C%20and%20seasonally%20or%20diurnally%20limited%20renewable%20sources.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20already%20know%20this.%20Why%20else%20would%20we%20Indians%20have%20argued%20for%20entitlements%20to%20burn%20more%20fossils%2C%20justified%20only%20by%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20economic%20dominance%20by%20having%20done%20it%20first%3F%20If%20we%20believed%20%E2%80%98renewables%E2%80%99%20were%20a%20complete%20answer%2C%20we%20would%20gladly%20leapfrog%20the%20need%20for%20combustible%20fossils%20and%20build%20the%20great%20and%20%E2%80%98clean%E2%80%99%20Indian%20industrial%20economy.%20But%20despite%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98hope%E2%80%99%20elites%20declaim%20around%20%E2%80%98greening%E2%80%99%20our%20energy%20systems%2C%20we%20intuitively%20understand%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20way%20to%20have%20the%20%E2%80%98developed%2C%E2%80%99%20capitalist-consumerist%20economy%20without%20breaking%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98renewable%E2%80%99%20energy%E2%80%94which%20is%20delivered%20to%20us%20only%20through%20installations%20that%20are%20%3Cem%3Enot%20at%20all%20renewable%3C%2Fem%3E%20but%20%3Cem%3Emust%20be%20built%20and%20re-built%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20every%20few%20decades%E2%80%94thus%20far%20deployed%20haven%E2%80%99t%20begun%20to%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fourworldindata.org%2Fgrapher%2Felectricity-prod-source-stacked%5C%22%3Eonly%20added%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20581px)%2085vw%2C%20581px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-300x212.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112945%2Fglobal-energy-substitution-1024x723.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700960%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22410%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERenewable%20energy%20sources%20haven%E2%80%99t%20reduced%20our%20demand%20for%20combustible%20fossils.%20They%20have%20only%20allowed%20us%20to%20increase%20our%20overall%20energy%20consumption.%20Chart%3A%20Our%20World%20in%20Data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20exposes%20the%20terrible%20reality%20that%20we%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20reduce%20our%20fossil%20fuel%20consumption%E2%80%94and%20associated%20carbon%20emissions%E2%80%94until%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jasonhickel.org%2Fblog%2F2023%2F11%2F24%2Fhow-popular-are-post-growth-and-post-capitalist-ideas%5C%22%3Estop%20growing%20the%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ending%20fossil-fuelled%20emissions%20means%20transitioning%20to%20a%20reduced%20energy-and-materials%20consumption%20economy.%20This%20requires%20simultaneously%20innovating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-022-04412-x%5C%22%3Ealternate%20modes%20of%20social%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provisioning%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20allows%20other%20living%20systems%20also%20to%20flourish.%20It%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20path%20forward.%20This%20means%20prioritizing%20the%20uses%20of%20a%20limited%20energy%20budget%20in%20a%20way%20that%20equitably%20benefits%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20people.%20And%20this%20implies%20austerity%20for%20the%20rich%E2%80%94indeed%2C%20a%20phase-out%20of%20wealth%20inequality%20and%20the%20mechanisms%20that%20create%20and%20maintain%20it.%20Taken%20together%2C%20this%20becomes%20an%20absolutely%20fundamental%20re-envisioning%20and%20restructuring%20of%20global%20society%20and%20the%20principles%20by%20which%20it%20functions%E2%80%94our%20social%20structures%2C%20value%20systems%2C%20identities%2C%20mythologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocieties%20do%20change%2C%20of%20course.%20They%20never%20stop%20changing%2C%20whether%20by%20consent%20or%20force%20of%20circumstance.%20For%20better%20or%20for%20worse.%20And%20that%20social%20change%20always%20entails%20an%20evolution%20in%20the%20stories%20we%20tell%20ourselves%2C%20for%20it%20is%20our%20stories%20that%20build%20the%20world%20we%20inhabit%E2%80%94as%20much%20as%20they%20can%20also%20blind%20us%20to%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20next%20essay%20will%20touch%20upon%20this%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710050720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10112000%2FIMG_2968.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Continuing%20to%20increase%20our%20dependency%20on%20these%20fossils%20in%20any%20way%20makes%20literally%20no%20Earthly%20sense.%20We%20must%20instead%20imagine%20a%20system%20that%20moves%20away%20from%20burning%20fossils%2C%20altogether%2C%20rap%C2%A0idly%20and%20completely.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'To%20Kill%20a%20Tiger'%20Chronicles%20a%20Father's%20Pursuit%20of%20Justice%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Strength%20of%20Women%20Around%20Him%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20glitzy%20Oscars%20scene%2C%20where%20gowns%20and%20tuxedos%20steal%20the%20show%2C%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20best%20documentary%20contenders%2C%20including%20Nisha%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20explore%20family%2C%20social%20justice%2C%20book%20banning%2C%20war%20and%20politics.%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20two-hour%20feature%20stands%20out%2C%20chronicling%20a%20father%E2%80%99s%20unwavering%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20for%20his%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20sat%20down%20to%20write%20a%20review%20of%20this%20heart-rattlingly%20urgent%20documentary%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fjharkhand-13-year-old-girl-killed-for-resisting-rape-attempt-in-godda%5C%22%3Enews%20%3C%2Fa%3Etrickled%20down%20about%20yet%20another%20killing%20of%2013-year-old%20girl.%20She%20was%20allegedly%20killed%20in%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Godda%20district%20after%20she%20resisted%20an%20attempt%20of%20rape%20by%20two%20men%20aged%2021%20who%20have%20confessed%20to%20committing%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20weighs%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20vast%20media%20universe%2C%20stories%20of%20sexual%20assault%20often%20fade%20away%2C%20lost%20in%20overloaded%20legal%20processes%20or%20swallowed%20by%20toxic%20masculinity.%20Yet%2C%20%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20A%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20cinematic%20documentary%2C%20purposefully%20unveils%20real-life%20stories%2C%20urging%20broader%20attention%20to%20the%20rampant%20epidemic%20of%20misogynistic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETending%20to%20the%20rice%20fields%2C%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20doting%20father%20to%20his%20daughter%2C%20the%20victim%20of%20a%20sexual%20assault%20in%202017%20%E2%80%93%20shares%20a%20poignant%20revelation%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20film.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20once%20told%2C%20%E2%80%98You%20can%E2%80%99t%20kill%20a%20tiger%20by%20yourself%2C'%E2%80%9D%20recounts%20Ranjit%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20replied%2C%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99ll%20show%20you%20how%20to%20kill%20a%20tiger%20all%20by%20yourself.%E2%80%99%20And%20so%2C%20I%20did.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20sets%20up%20the%20narrative%20arc%20of%20the%20tale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Emotional%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForged%20over%20the%20course%20of%20eight%20years%2C%20the%20documentary%2C%20winner%20of%20more%20than%2020%20awards%20at%20festivals%20around%20the%20world%2C%20highlights%20the%20pervasive%20and%20deeply%20rooted%20nature%20of%20male%20violence%20against%20females%20ingrained%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20our%20society.%20How%20does%20one%20tell%20such%20a%20story%3F%20Caught%20in%20the%20spotlight%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20stance%20captivates%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20Srijan%20Foundation%2C%20an%20NGO%20dedicated%20to%20sensitising%20men%20and%20boys%20about%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20They%20see%20in%20Ranjit%20a%20symbol%20for%20their%20cause%2C%20a%20beacon%20of%20inspiration%20for%20other%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20Delhi-born%20Canadian%20director%20Nisha%20Pahuja%20says%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%20%3C%2Fem%3Eactually%20started%20off%20as%20an%20entirely%20different%20film.%20That%20film%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESend%C2%A0Us%20Your%20Brother%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20a%20more%20pointed%20and%20direct%20exploration%20of%20Indian%20masculinity.%20The%20focus%20of%20the%20original%20work%20was%20Mahendra%20Kumar%2C%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20activist%20who%20has%20a%20key%2C%20albeit%20minor%2C%20role%20in%20the%20film.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20as%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20story%20emerged%20from%20a%20programme%20led%20by%20Mahendra%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20the%20director%20recognised%20its%20potential%20as%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20backbone%2C%20with%20his%20work%20and%20personal%20life%20adding%20a%20broader%20context%20to%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20Kill%20a%20Tiger%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Echarts%20the%20emotional%20journey%20of%20an%20ordinary%20man%20thrown%20into%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20%E2%80%93%20a%20father%20whose%20love%20for%20his%20daughter%20forces%20a%20social%20reckoning%20that%20will%20reverberate%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20The%20allure%20of%20this%20approach%20stemmed%20from%20its%20simplicity.%20It%20offers%20a%20continuity%20to%20a%20rich%20body%20of%20works%20that%20Pahuja%20has%20undertaken%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20like%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20short%20film%20for%20%3Cem%3EGlobal%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20news%20and%20current%20affairs%20programme%2016%C3%979%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Bus%20Outrage%E2%80%99%2C%20investigating%20flaws%20in%20the%20justice%20system%20in%20India%20following%20the%20brutal%202012%20gang%20rape%20and%20murder%20of%20a%20young%20woman%20on%20a%20bus%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20It%20was%20a%20recipient%20of%20an%20Amnesty%20International%20media%20award%20for%20Canadian%20journalism%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FmC6-igJ_WWM%3Fsi%3D6mZeRndBdacBfDeV%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%20approached%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20complex%20situation%20with%20a%20keen%20understanding%20of%20its%20layered%20sensitivity.%20With%20prior%20experience%20directing%20films%20in%20India%2C%20notably%20%3Cem%3EThe%20World%20Before%20Her%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2012)%20that%20juxtaposed%20the%20competition%20among%20women%20aspiring%20to%20be%20Miss%20India%20with%20Hindu%20nationalists%20defending%20their%20beliefs%20(awarded%20Best%20Canadian%20Feature%20at%20the%20Hot%20Docs%20Canadian%20International%20Documentary%20Festival)%2C%20she%20was%20mindful%20not%20to%20take%20sides%20in%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20fabric%2C%20intimate%20scenes%20from%20village%20gatherings%20reveal%20a%20spectrum%20of%20perspectives%2C%20featuring%20voices%20even%20from%20the%20fathers%20of%20the%20accused.%20Yet%2C%20as%20the%20legal%20proceedings%20persist%2C%20a%20faction%20of%20villagers%20resorts%20to%20coercive%20tactics%20against%20Ranjit%20%E2%80%93%20employing%20emotional%20manipulation%2C%20proffering%20bribes%20and%20escalating%20to%20threats%20of%20arson%20and%20murder.%20This%20mounting%20tension%20culminates%20in%20an%20increasing%20animosity%20directed%20at%20the%20film%20crew%20earnestly%20documenting%20these%20unfolding%20and%20unsettling%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPahuja%E2%80%99s%20husband%2C%20Mrinal%20Desai%2C%20wields%20the%20camera%20like%20a%20poet%E2%80%99s%20pen.%20He%20deftly%20captures%20the%20village%E2%80%99s%20serenity%2C%20meandering%20through%20its%20tranquil%20spaces%20and%20deciphering%20the%20unspoken%20dialect%20of%20gazes%20%E2%80%93%20all%20the%20while%20encapsulating%20the%20hidden%20subterranean%20explosiveness%20simmering%20beneath%20the%20narrative%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20As%20if%20drawing%20inspiration%20from%20the%20locale%2C%20a%20mining%20town%20famed%20for%20its%20rich%20mineral%20veins%2C%20the%20cinematographer%20moulds%20haptic%20images%2C%20extracting%20their%20nuanced%20meanings%20and%20tensions.%20The%20cinematic%20shots%20in%20the%20labyrinth%20of%20courts%20in%20Ranchi%20reminds%20one%20of%20his%20early%20work%20in%20Chaitanya%20Tamhane%E2%80%99s%20Marathi-language%20courtroom%20drama%2C%20%3Cem%3ECourt%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cinematic%20narrative%20commences%20with%20Ranjit%20articulating%20the%20profound%20experience%20of%20welcoming%20his%20daughter%2C%20Kiran%2C%20into%20the%20world.%20He%20cloaks%20her%20in%20the%20entirety%20of%20his%20affection%2C%20challenging%20the%20notion%20that%20love%20transcends%20the%20confines%20of%20material%20reality.%20With%20her%20penchant%20for%20narrative-driven%20films%2C%20Pahuja%20crafts%20intricately%20woven%20worlds%20that%20captivate%20with%20their%20visual%20splendour%20%E2%80%93%20a%20close-up%20of%20Kiran%20braiding%20her%20hair%20with%20colourful%20ribbons%20%E2%80%93%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Spanish%20filmmaker%20Isabel%20Coixet.%20More%20so%2C%20it%20is%20particularly%20apparent%20in%20her%20silent%20portrayal%20of%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20highlighting%20her%20steadfast%20silent%20presence%20and%20the%20nuanced%20dynamics%20of%20her%20relationship%20with%20her%20husband%20Ranjit.%20The%20deliberate%20manner%20in%20which%20she%20guides%20and%20supports%20him%20during%20his%20moments%20of%20vulnerability%20underscores%20her%20inherent%20strength.%C2%A0%20Wrestling%20with%20the%20profound%20intricacies%20of%20human%20existence%20remains%20a%20constant%20in%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20exploration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20National%20Film%20Board%20of%20Canada-funded%20documentary%2C%20her%20storytelling%2C%20delicately%20rendered%2C%20possesses%20a%20distinctly%20feminine%20and%20sensual%20allure.%20That%20made%20me%20think%20of%20Jane%20Campion%2C%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20contemporary%20filmmakers%2C%20and%20her%20classic%20short%20%E2%80%93%20a%20tightly%20controlled%20nine-minute%20drama%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EPeel%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1982)%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Piano%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1993)%20and%20more%20recent%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Power%20of%20the%20Dog%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021).%20Though%20a%20tale%20of%20the%20father%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%2C%20this%20film%20is%20predominantly%20concerned%20with%20female%20characters%20struggling%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20recognised%20and%20understood.%20The%20intricacies%20of%20other%20figures%20in%20the%20tale%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20the%20Ward%20Member%2C%20Ranjit%E2%80%99s%20wife%20Jaganti%2C%20and%2C%20most%20notably%2C%20his%20daughter%20Kiran%20%E2%80%93%20unfold%20in%20delicate%20layers.%20While%20Kiran%20undeniably%20survives%20a%20brutal%20crime%2C%20her%20character%20transcends%20simplistic%20victimhood%2C%20revealing%20nuanced%20facets%20that%20enrich%20the%20narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEthics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Pahuja%E2%80%99s%20narrative%20ethics%20govern%20her%20art.%20%E2%80%9CDiscussing%20morality%20without%20considering%20the%20ethics%20of%20filming%20a%20survivor%2C%20especially%20a%20child%2C%20would%20be%20a%20lapse%20on%20my%20part.%20Initially%20hiding%20Kiran%E2%80%99s%20identity%20complied%20with%20Indian%20law%20and%20felt%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20However%2C%20grappling%20with%20the%20prevailing%20cultural%20stigma%2C%20she%20questions%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20not%20showing%20her%2C%20am%20I%20perpetuating%20the%20bias%20I%20critique%3F%20Yet%2C%20imposing%20my%20perspective%20on%20a%20vulnerable%20child%20feels%20unjust.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20emerging%20to%20be%20a%20thorny%20issue.%20Anna%20M.M.%20Vetticad%2C%20author%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Adventures%20of%20an%20Intrepid%20Film%20Critic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20points%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.himalmag.com%2Fculture%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-oscars-india-rape-pocso%5C%22%3Eethical%20and%20legal%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%20inherent%20in%20the%20making%20of%20the%20film.%20The%20issue%20of%20filming%20a%20minor%20rape%20victim%20makes%20it%20vulnerable%20for%20the%20filmmaker%2C%20given%20the%20stringent%20guidelines%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act%202012.%20The%20victim%E2%80%99s%20parent%E2%80%99s%20permission%20does%20not%20suffice%2C%20one%20has%20to%20get%20a%20directive%20from%20a%20special%20court%20if%20it%20deems%20in%20its%20view%20that%20such%20disclosure%20aligns%20with%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%20involved.%20Meanwhile%20another%20Canadian%20filmmaker%2C%20Leena%20Manimekalai%2C%20has%20patently%20dismissed%20the%20film%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLeenaManimekali%2Fstatus%2F1746228215671079068%5C%22%3Ea%20classic%20example%20of%20a%20settler%20colonist%20gaze%20on%20an%20indigenous%20child%20survivor%20of%20gang%20rape%20in%20a%20developing%20country%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%2C%20Kiran%20existed%20as%20both%20a%20child%20and%20a%20survivor.%20Today%20in%20her%2020th%20year%2C%20Kiran%20is%20so%20much%20more.%20She%20stands%20tall%20and%20looks%20out%20to%20a%20brighter%20future%20and%20wonders%20about%20falling%20in%20love%20and%20what%20she%20will%20tell%20her%20beloved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20my%20hope%20that%20collectively%20we%20empower%20her%20and%20support%20her%20healing%20as%20part%20of%20this%20film%E2%80%99s%20journey%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20a%20journey%20with%20impact%20at%20its%20heart%2C%20and%20one%20that%E2%80%99s%20being%20planned%20carefully%20and%20strategically%20with%20lawyers%2C%20documentary%20impact%20strategists%2C%20therapists%20and%20an%20advisory%20council%20made%20up%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20human%20rights%20organisations%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Pahuja.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20list%20of%20executive%20producers%20that%20are%20attached%20to%20this%20film%20including%20Dev%20Patel%2C%20Mindy%20Kailing%2C%20poet%20Rupi%20Kaur%2C%20Dr%20Atul%20Gawande%20and%20Priyanka%20Chopra%20Jonas%2C%20to%20ensure%20this%20story%20does%20what%20it%20can%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20distressing%20news%20of%20yet%20another%20assault%20on%20a%2013-year%20old%20girl%20in%20the%20same%20region%20filtering%20through%2C%20the%20sickening%20irony%20piles%20up%2C%20each%20layer%20adding%20a%20punch%20to%20the%20gut%20within%20the%20narrative%20of%20this%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENarendra%20Pachkh%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ed%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A9%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20critic%20and%20writer%20who%C2%A0splits%20his%20time%20between%20Toronto%2C%20London%20and%20Geneva.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710049542000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F10111355%2FTo-Kill-a-Tiger-02.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fto-kill-a-tiger-nisha-pahuja%22%2C%22summary%2